I walked in on a Monday around 2pm and they were not busy at all. The entree that I wanted was empty, and they didn't even start cooking it until I ordered it. (This I honestly didn't have much of a problem with because at this point, I know that its at least fresh! ) I wait for about 10 minutes or so, and get my food. I then proceed to go back to work, so I can enjoy a nice desk meal. Taking a few bites of everything I come to the steak and this bite is a little big, so I cut it in half and it is completely raw in the middle. Thinking its a fluke, I try another piece and its the same thing! At this point, I'm a little irritated and extremely grossed out, so I call the manager, Danielle. She asked that I bring it back down to the store with my receipt. At this point I'm still just slightly frustrated but I also understand that things happen. I am just a few blocks from the store so its a quick walk. When I get there, they tell me that the manager left to go to the bank. That's where the one star comes into place. You ask a customer to come down and then you leave for over a half an hour and then proceed to tell me that its MY FAULT that I came back in so quickly!? My entire lunch consisted of eating raw meat and waiting for the manager to get back AFTER she asked me to come down! I'm sorry, but common sense should have told you that, that was simply a stupid idea!
